    "There are many theories, and multifold interdisciplinary readings, of the notion of loneliness.",
    "Weiss (33) has stressed a methodological flaw of loneliness research as follows:",
    "What seems to me wrong with many current \"definitions\" of loneliness is that they are insufficiently sensitive to loneliness's status as a real phenomenon.",
    "(…) They define it by the conditions that might theoretically give rise to it.",
    "(…) Other definitions of loneliness suggest a theoretical idea of what is at the heart of loneliness."
